115-kD protein preferentially localized in the nucleus and its
periphery.";
"Fission yeast pap1-dependent transcription is negatively regulated by
an essential nuclear protein, crm1.";
"Leptomycin B targets a regulatory cascade of crm1, a fission yeast
nuclear protein, involved in control of higher order chromosome
structure and gene expression.";
"Leptomycin B inactivates CRM1/exportin 1 by covalent modification at
