-!- FUNCTION: Receptor for the leucine-rich nuclear export signal
    (NES).
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Nucleus. Note=Localized in the nucleus and
    at its periphery.
-!- MISCELLANEOUS: Cellular target of leptomycin B (LMB), a nuclear
    export inhibitor. LMB alkylates Cys-529 leading to CRM1
    inactivation.
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the exportin family.
-!- SIMILARITY: Contains 1 importin N-terminal domain.
